    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow employees to claim the 80% income support directly from the Government",
        "additional_details": "The Government should change this scheme so that employees affected by coronavirus, who are currently employed or have been in the last three months, can directly claim 80% of their wages from the Government, without this needing to be claimed by their employer.",
        "background": "The Government\u2019s Coronavirus Job Retention Scheme pays employers a grant to cover 80% of the wages, up to \u00a32,500 a month, of employees who have been put on temporary leave.",
